properties.areaDesc: Larimer and Boulder Counties Between 6000 and 9000 Feet; Jefferson and West Douglas Counties Above  6000 Feet/Gilpin/Clear Creek/Northeast Park Counties Below 9000 Feet
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 6 at 4:50PM MST until January 7 at 12:00PM MST by NWS Denver CO
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 25 to 40 mph with gusts up to 75 mph expected.

* WHERE...Larimer and Boulder Counties Between 6000 and 9000
Feet and Jefferson and West Douglas Counties Above 6000
Feet/Gilpin/Clear Creek/Northeast Park Counties Below 9000
Feet.

* WHEN...Until noon MST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result. Travel will be difficult for high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Strong winds may lead to property damage. Hazardous driving
conditions due to powerful cross winds will pose a serious risk
for drivers, especially for light weight and high profile
vehicles. Loose outdoor items should be brought inside or secured
properly.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON MST TUESDAY
